39 // Class to specify a box constraint on a vector-valued control variable.
40 //

44 #define FASTRACK_CONTROL_VECTOR_BOUND_BOX_H

46 #include <fastrack/control/control_bound.h>
47 #include <fastrack/control/scalar_bound_interval.h>

49 namespace fastrack {
50 namespace control {
51 
52 class VectorBoundBox : public ControlBound<VectorXd> {
53 public:
54  ~VectorBoundBox() {}
55  explicit VectorBoundBox(const VectorXd &min, const VectorXd &max)
56  : ControlBound(), min_(min), max_(max) {
57  if (min_.size() != max_.size())
58  throw std::runtime_error("Inconsistent bound dimensions.");
59  }
60 
61  // Accessors.
62  inline const VectorXd &Min() const { return min_; }
63  inline const VectorXd &Max() const { return max_; }
64 
65  // Derived classes must be able to check whether a query is inside the bound.
66  inline bool Contains(const VectorXd &query) const {
67  if (min_.size() != query.size()) {
68  ROS_ERROR("VectorBoundBox: incorrect query dimension.");
69  return false;
70  }
71 
72  for (size_t ii = 0; ii < min_.size(); ii++) {
73  if (min_(ii) > query(ii) || query(ii) > max_(ii))
74  return false;
75  }
76 
77  return true;
78  }
79 
80  // Derived classes must be able to compute the projection of a vector
81  // (represented as the templated type) onto the surface of the bound.
82  // NOTE: We will treat this vector as emanating from the natural origin
83  // of the bound so that it constitutes a meaningful direction with respect
84  // to that origin.
85  inline VectorXd ProjectToSurface(const VectorXd &query) const {
86  if (min_.size() != query.size()) {
87  ROS_ERROR("VectorBoundBox: incorrect query dimension.");
88  return VectorXd::Zero(min_.size());
89  }
90 
91  VectorXd projection(min_.size());
92  for (size_t ii = 0; ii < min_.size(); ii++)
93  projection(ii) = (query(ii) >= 0.0) ? max_(ii) : min_(ii);
94 
95  return projection;
96  }
97 
98 private:
99  // Lower and upper bounds..
100  const VectorXd min_, max_;
101 }; //\class ControlBound

104 } // namespace fastrack
